# Component Development

## Directory Structure

Each component lives under `packages/components/{kebab-name}/`:

```
{component-name}/
  index.ts              # default export + .install + type re-exports
  src/
    index.vue           # root SFC
    {component}.ts      # props/emits interfaces (ProTableProps, etc.)
    defaults.ts         # Options API prop definitions (when using defineComponent)
    composables/        # component-specific hooks
    components/         # sub-components and svg icons
```

Base building blocks go in `packages/base/` with the same `index.ts` + `src/` layout.

## Entry File Pattern

```ts
import type { App } from 'vue'
import MyComponent from './src/index.vue'

MyComponent.install = (app: App) => {
  app.component(MyComponent.name as string, MyComponent)
}

export default MyComponent
export * from './src/my-component'
export type MyComponentInstance = InstanceType<typeof MyComponent>
```

## SFC Conventions

- Root component `name` must match export (e.g. `'ProTable'`, `'ProForm'`)
- CSS classes use BEM: `.pro-table__form`, `.pro-table__toolbar`
- Styles: `<style lang="less" scoped>`
- Template comments mark sections: `<!-- Search form -->`, `<!-- start -->` / `<!-- end -->`
- Expose imperative API via `defineExpose` or `expose()` in setup

## Props Definition

Two patterns coexist — match the surrounding component:

**Script setup** (preferred for new work):

```ts
const props = withDefaults(defineProps<ProFormProps>(), proFormPropsDefaults)
```

**defineComponent** (ProTable):

```ts
// defaults.ts — PropType definitions with JSDoc
// pro-table.ts — TypeScript interfaces
// index.vue — props: defaultProps
```

Keep interface (`pro-*.ts`) and runtime props (`defaults.ts`) in sync.

## Sub-components

- Place in `src/components/`; use PascalCase filenames (`ColumnSettings.vue`)
- SVG icons in `src/components/svg/`
- JSX render components as `.tsx` (e.g. `Submitter.tsx`)

## Custom Rendering

Use `CustomRender` from `packages/base/custom-render` for VNode/JSX render props:

```vue
<CustomRender :render="() => formItem.renderField?.({ form, formItem })" />
```

Never inline render functions directly in templates.
